      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 324: savePublishedAddressSettings validates and saves address and port together, but the UI edits them in separate screens. If the untouched paired field is currently empty/invalid, the edited field is discarded on disappear, so a user cannot enter the two required values incrementally from an empty configuration. Save each field independently, or pass the edited field into the save method so only that value is validated and persisted. Suggested shape:\\n```suggestion\\nfunc savePublishedAddress() {\\n    guard !publishedAddress.isEmpty else {\\n        publishedAddress \u003d getStringState(for: ConfigKey.publishedAddress)\\n        return\\n    }\\n    accountService.setAccountProperty(property: ConfigKeyModel(withKey: .publishedAddress), value: publishedAddress, accountId: account.id)\\n}\\n\\nfunc savePublishedPort() {\\n    guard AccountSettings.isValid(publishedPort, in: AccountSettings.publishedPortRange) else {\\n        publishedPort \u003d getStringState(for: ConfigKey.publishedPort)\\n        return\\n    }\\n    accountService.setAccountProperty(property: ConfigKeyModel(withKey: .publishedPort), value: publishedPort, accountId: account.id)\\n}\\n```",
